            "body": "> But rplugins are more like for RPC support and not about UI, so `vim.ui` wouldn't be a good choice. I can suggest: `vim.remote`\r\n\r\nI suggested `vim.ui` because introducing something like `vim.providers` just seems pointless because most \"providers\" really _are_ user-facing interfaces (\"UI\"). The python/ruby/node providers exist to provide `:pydo`, `:rubydo`, etc, which are directly user-facing features. OTOH, they also provide API, so it would be a stretch...",
